  "sitemap_lastmod": null,
  "text": "Science Laboratories\nThe science laboratories are located on the 4th and 5th floors of the south hall of the campus. More than twenty science laboratories and supporting instrument rooms cover various scientific disciplines such as physics, chemistry, biology, electrical, and computer engineering. They are equipped with world-class experimental equipment and complete supporting facilities.\nThe laboratories serve the experimental teaching of basic courses in various disciplines such as physics, chemistry, biology, electrical engineering, and computer engineering, as well as specialized lab courses such as organic chemistry, advanced cell biology, genetics, computer embedded systems, and digital logic, and other elective experimental teaching. It also serves as a platform for students' independent studies and capstones. After completing safety and instrument operation training, students gain access to advanced precision equipment for scientific research. Under the guidance of faculty and lab specialists, they engage in hands-on exploration, contributing to scientific discovery and innovation.\nLaboratory Safety\nLaboratory Management\nChemical Management\nThe Laboratory Management Department is fully committed to maintaining high standards of quality, overall safety, and compliance within the laboratory while ensuring smooth and efficient operation. We implement complementary management regulations and safety policies to protect the safety of the students, faculty, staff, and the university community and provide various experimental equipment and instruments. Our efforts provide students with hands-on experience with course concepts and the opportunity to explore different experimental methods, ensure the well-being of laboratory personnel, and meet regulatory requirements.\nLaboratory News\nQuick Links:\nBiology lab safety quiz\nChemistry lab safety quiz\nElectrical Engineering lab safety quiz\nEnergy and Environment lab safety quiz\nGenetics lab safety quiz\nPhysics lab safety quiz\nContact Us\nEmail:shanghai.labs@nyu.edu",
