      "type": "p",
      "text": "The science laboratories are located on the 4th and 5th floors of the south hall of the campus. More than twenty science laboratories and supporting instrument rooms cover various scientific disciplines such as physics, chemistry, biology, electrical, and computer engineering. They are equipped with world-class experimental equipment and complete supporting facilities."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "The laboratories serve the experimental teaching of basic courses in various disciplines such as physics, chemistry, biology, electrical engineering, and computer engineering, as well as specialized lab courses such as organic chemistry, advanced cell biology, genetics, computer embedded systems, and digital logic, and other elective experimental teaching. It also serves as a platform for students' independent studies and capstones. After completing safety and instrument operation training, students gain access to advanced precision equipment for scientific research. Under the guidance of faculty and lab specialists, they engage in hands-on exploration, contributing to scientific discovery and innovation."
    },
